Pinus palustris

   [2542.jpg]
   Authority Mill.
   Family Pinopsida:Pinaceae
   Synonyms Pinus australis Michx.
   Common names longleaf pine, fat pine, fatwood pine, Florida pine, heart
   pine, broom pine, long-straw pine, pinheiro da Florida
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 2542

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A medium sized, light crowned, evergreen tree
   reaching a height of 25-40 m. USES An oil is obtained from the bark and
   used as a herbicide and desinfectant, in soaps, insecticides,
   deodorants, polishes, and in perfumery-grade terpineol, anethole,
   fenchone, and camphor, and in turpentine and rosin. Its timber are used
   for construction, boat building, and boxes but has a problem with resin
   checks. Roundwood is used for transmission poles, fence posts,
   longfiber pulp, fuel and charcoal. It produces a resin. It is also
   planted as an ornamental and for shelter, and erosion control. KILLING
   T Moderately frost resistant. GROWING PERIOD Perennial. COMMON NAMES
   Longleaf pine. FURTHER INF Scientific synonym: P. australis. Longleaf
   pine can be found at elevations from sea level to 1500 m. The tree
   occur naturally within the latitudinal range of 27-36Â°N. It is windfirm
   and relatively fire-resistant. Annual wood production potential is 6-12
   m3/ha.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Webb D 1984 pp 222 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, PH, DRA, LIG, KTMP, USE]
   INSPIRE species 139 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, PH, DRA, LIG, KTMP, USE]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 97 [USE, LIG, TEXT, RAIN, KTMP, TEMP, DEP]

